rComments: His lectures are really engaging. However, it is ironic that as someone who preaches the importance of being open to change, he is surprisingly not very welcoming of new ideas himself.

very frustrating experience. treats subjective and creative topics as if there is a perfect answer. better know exactly what he's thinking or you will lose marks. studying is counter productive because examples given in class (i.e. vision statements) are not representative of what is considered a good answer. so good luck.
Attend lectures and take notes. Amazing class discussions that practically cover all of exam material. Easy marking for projects.

Peter Lloyd is a great prof, even though lectures are 3 hours long, he makes them more interesting by getting the class to do little ice breakers kinda. He also gives great feedback on assignments, and is willing to talk about business ideas outside of class. Class itself is pretty interesting but the assignment essays were long.

Prof Peter Lloyd is one of the best profs Ive ever had. As a 3rd yr student, Ive had a plethora of profs & his teaching style is by far the best. His anecdotal-discussion style is not only informative but actually engaging! Youll look forward to each class-covers exam&test material in class, so youre set! Get ready for great grades & learning!

Lectures were long but the professor let us out early sometimes, he cares about the student and is always there to help. It is a very interesting and informative class especially with the professors vast experience in many fields. Assignments (projects) were long and tedious but were marked fairly.

Peter Lloyd was an outstanding professor who really cares about his students. He will answer any question you have about the course. The assignments were long but if you put in the effort, he graded them very fairly. I would take Peter for another class in the future!
He is a new prof and doesn't really teach, he just reads the slides and talks about one slide for 50 minutes about his work experience. Wouldn't recommend his class as an elective.
